WHAT IS A RUCK CLUB - CHECKLIST

INTRODUCTION
A ruck club is a group of individuals who come together to participate in rucking, which is walking with a weighted backpack. This activity builds strength, endurance, and camaraderie.

CORE PRINCIPLES
☐ Inclusivity: Welcoming individuals of all fitness levels and backgrounds.
☐ Safety: Prioritizing proper form and injury prevention.
☐ Consistency: Regular meetings to build habit and progress.
☐ Community: Fostering a supportive and motivating environment.
☐ Purpose: Aligning rucking with personal and collective goals.

PRACTICAL CHECKLIST
☐ Define the club's mission and goals.
☐ Choose a regular meeting time and location.
☐ Establish safety guidelines and equipment requirements.
☐ Create a communication channel (e.g., WhatsApp group, email list).
☐ Plan the first ruck event and invite participants.